The paper deals with the problem of unsupervised learning of category-specific 3D keypoints from point sets, which involves shape analysis and representation learning. This makes it likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also deals with the problem of establishing correspondences across objects, which involves graph matching and optimization, making it relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach that uses a symmetry prior to learn stable keypoints, which involves modeling and inference, making it relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
